---
intent: >
  Add the AIDEMD wordmark and catchphrase as the dominant brand identity element
  at the very top of the landing page, above the InstallHero. Update page titles
  to use the product catchphrase instead of the methodology acronym expansion,
  and fix the layout.tsx description to reference AIDE (methodology), not AIDEMD.
---

## Plan

### Step 1: Create the Wordmark component

Read: `coding-playbook/client/components.md` (component file structure, no-padding rule,
semantic HTML), `coding-playbook/foundations/conventions.md` (naming, JSDoc, function ordering)

Create folder and file: `src/components/LandingPage/Wordmark/index.tsx`

- [x] Create a new component `Wordmark` as the default export.
- [x] The component renders a `<div>` (not `<header>` — InstallHero already uses
      `<header>` for the page hero; this is a brand identity element, not a page
      header) containing:
      - An `<h1>` with the text "AIDEMD" — this is the dominant visual. Style it
        large and bold: `text-6xl sm:text-8xl font-bold tracking-tighter text-zinc-100`.
        The h1 carries the product name as the page's primary heading.
      - A `<p>` beneath it with the text "Code is ephemeral. Intent is law." — the
        catchphrase in smaller text: `text-lg sm:text-xl text-zinc-500 tracking-wide`.
- [x] The outer `<div>` uses `flex flex-col items-center text-center` for centering
      and `py-16 sm:py-24 px-4` for vertical spacing. No horizontal padding on the
      outermost element per the no-padding rule — but since this is a full-width
      centered text block (not a card composed into a parent grid), the `px-4` is
      the page-level safety margin against viewport edges, not layout padding. This
      matches InstallHero's own `px-4` on its outer element.
- [x] Add JSDoc on the component: one line explaining this is the product brand
      identity element shown at the very top of the landing page.
- [x] No props. No interactivity. No imports beyond React (if needed — likely not
      since this is a plain functional component with no hooks).

The component is intentionally minimal — two text elements, no logic. It exists as
its own folder/index.tsx per progressive disclosure so the LandingPage orchestrator's
import list reads as the page composition at a glance.

Spec trace: LP spec `outcomes.desired[0]` ("The AIDEMD wordmark appears as the
dominant visual element at the very top of the page"); LP spec `outcomes.undesired[0]`
("A header or product label that reads 'AIDE' without the 'MD' suffix");
LP spec `outcomes.undesired[1]` ("A persistent top navigation bar" — this is NOT
a nav bar, it is a brand identity element).

